<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
        <script>
            $(document).ready(function(){
              $("#b1").click(function(){
                  $("div").slideDown("slow");
                });
                $("#b2").click(function(){
                  $("div").slideUp(3000);
                });
                $("#b3").click(function(){
                  $("div").slideToggle("slow");
                });
            });
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>slideUp(), slideDown() and slideToggle() method</h1>
        <div id="demo1" style="background-color:green;padding:20px;margin-top:80px;">
            <p>This is some text.</p>
            <p>This is some text.</p>
            <p>This is some text.</p>
        </div>
        <br><br>
        <button id="b2">slideUp</button>
        <button id="b1">slideDown</button>
        <button id="b3">slideToggle</button>
        <br><br><br><br>
        <p><b>slideUp()</b> method is used to silde up(hide) content.</p>
        <p><b>slideDown()</b> method is used to slide down(show) content.</p>
        <p><b>slideToggle()</b> method is used to silde up(hide) and slide down(show) content both.</p>
    </body>
</html>
